  "summary": "Changes the Ebony Mail to Light Armor.",
  "descriptionHtml": "So you\\'ve just completed one of the only stealth quests in the game and you have been rewarded with what may be the best sneaking armor out there, only to find that it\\'s Heavy Armor?  Not a great reward for a typical sneaky character.  This mod alters Ebony Mail to be Light Armor and works with all perks associated with it.  The Matching Set perk will function if you are wearing all Dragonscale pieces in your other equipment slots.\r\n\r\nIf you\\'d rather match with the other Dragonscale pieces, I have included a version of the Ebony Mail named Shadow Mail that uses the Dragonscale Armor model.  It replaces Ebony Mail, so it can be obtained in game in the same way.  Both armor pieces use the Dragon Armor smithing perk for upgrades.\r\n\r\nTo install, extract to your Data folder, and check the esp in Data Files in the game launcher.  If Data Files is grayed out, add \r\n\r\nbEnableFileSelection=1 \r\n\r\nto C:\\\\Users\\\\*Your User Name*\\\\Documents\\\\My Games\\\\Skyrim\\\\SkyrimPrefs.ini. \r\n\r\nUse one esp or the other.  They are not compatible.\r\n\r\n------------------\r\nChange Log\r\n------------------\r\n-  Added Unenchated version.\r\nv 1.1  -  Updated the weight and armor rating to be more in line with light armor.  They now have the same stats as Dragonscale.",
